==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*wadja-'', from Indo-European ''*u̯adh-''.

'''Germanic cognates:''' Old Frisian [[wedd#Old Frisian|wedd]], Old Saxon [[weddi]] (Dutch [[wedde]]), Old High German [[wetti]] (German [[Wette]]), Old Norse [[veð]] (Swedish [[vad]]), Gothic [[𐍅𐌰𐌳𐌹]].

'''Indo-European cognates:''' Latin [[vas]], Lithuanian [[vãdas]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /wɛd/

===Noun===
'''wedd''' ''n''
# a [[pledge]] or [[contract]]

